1
00:00:27,020 --> 00:00:29,340
(Dungeon Pass)

2
00:00:29,340 --> 00:00:30,940
(Loading)

3
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:34,020
(The Truth)

4
00:00:35,020 --> 00:00:39,060
=The Truth (Season 4)=

5
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:40,960
Do you think anyone this season

6
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:43,160
will find the key piece of evidence?

7
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:45,060
Good luck, players.

8
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:46,080
If someone finds it,

9
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,160
what prize should we give them?

10
00:00:49,060 --> 00:00:51,580
The system has unlocked
the Wish Pool feature.

11
00:00:51,580 --> 00:00:52,660
(Wish Pool Unlocked)
Players may make a wish.

12
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:54,520
(I have a wish)

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,000
Go ahead.

14
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,480
I wish for a hundred Lights On Cards.

15
00:00:59,120 --> 00:00:59,880
How about we just

16
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:01,520
get you a flashlight instead, bro?

17
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:02,600
No, wait.

18
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,160
(Withdraws a wish)
I want a high-powered flashlight.

19
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:07,280
A high-powered flashlight, huh?

20
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,080
(You really know how to exploit a loophole)
Okay.

21
00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:09,360
What if that flashlight,

22
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,760
I turn it on and
it still can't light up anything?

23
00:01:10,760 --> 00:01:11,920
Like a candle light, right?

24
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:13,600
Like one of those
counterfeit-detecting UV pens.

25
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,480
If I find the key evidence...

26
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:19,920
Rewarding you to do

27
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:20,680
ten solo missions.

28
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,400
Reward Ding Chengxin
to do a solo mission

29
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,240
(Brotherly love)
in pitch black.

30
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:25,040
Absolutely terrifying.

31
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,560
That wish hurts others and helps no one.

32
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,880
I think you should reconsider

33
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,960
(Just wants to stir things up)
your own wish.

34
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:31,320
I'm just kidding, bro.

35
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,200
I'm messing with you.

36
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:34,160
I want a flashlight with a stun baton
attached to it.

37
00:01:34,420 --> 00:01:35,780
(Starts swinging at everyone on sight)

38
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,480
I won't be able to tell
who my teammates are.

39
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,360
The person in front of me is Zhou Keyu.

40
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:41,160
You're Zhou Keyu, right?

41
00:01:44,860 --> 00:01:46,260
(Teasing is fun)

42
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:46,880
I want a card

43
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:47,920
that lets me

44
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:50,060
assign a solo mission
to anyone I choose.

45
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,500
(Joins the targeting team)
Can I?

46
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:52,200
Sure.

47
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:54,780
(This is definitely coming for me,
isn't it?)

48
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,360
Look at Ding's eyes.

49
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,600
This is definitely aimed at me.

50
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,300
(Already saw through it)

51
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,440
I'll think about it.

52
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:03,880
I don't really have any wish.

53
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:04,600
Let me think.

54
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:05,120
Maybe a skill upgrade.

55
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,880
Maybe buy you a bracelet instead?

56
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:08,960
Something material.

57
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,440
Let's go with material rewards.

58
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,040
I think something more fun
would be better.

59
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,160
Let the other guests

60
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,920
post a Weibo praising me.

61
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,960
That doesn't even need a reward,
they can just do it.

62
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,040
No, isn't that fun?

63
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:25,320
That's too formal.

64
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,960
How about other guests...

65
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:30,200
doing a 2-minute livestream
praising you?

66
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,960
(How about this?)

67
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:32,920
Join my fan community.

68
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,040
(Fan mode activated)

69
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:34,880
Become your hardcore fan.

70
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:35,960
Level-10 supporter.

71
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,640
Even carry your lightstick.

72
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,120
Alright, then let's do this.

73
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,440
Go check in on my fan community
for three days.

74
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:41,920
No problem, right?

75
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:42,360
No problem.

76
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:42,760
Okay.

77
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:43,360
Absolutely fine.

78
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:43,880
No problem.

79
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,000
Alright, let's settle this.

80
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,280
This is fun.

81
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,880
If someone finds it,
can the gold keys stack directly?

82
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,520
Give three keys.

83
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,520
I think it can be doubled.

84
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:57,600
Three keys?

85
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,440
Doubling should be fine, right?

86
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,360
Instant doubling.

87
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:00,200
I want to check...

88
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,000
Double existing gold keys?

89
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:02,440
Yes, double what you already have.

90
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:03,960
So if you have four or five,

91
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,360
that could instantly become
eight or ten.

92
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,520
(That would feel pretty good)
Yeah.

93
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,920
Yeah, straight to the top.

94
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,200
Might as well give you
three keys outright.

95
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,360
No, I don't think that's meaningful.

96
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,560
Adding keys isn't that useful.

97
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,080
That's pointless.

98
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,480
Money would be more practical, right?

99
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:15,920
No,

100
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:16,840
(We don't have to be that realistic)
wait.

101
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,040
You want something practical, right?

102
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,400
(Gold keys can only be exchanged for skill cards)
If a player finds key evidence,

103
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,880
(Not counted in rankings)
they receive one extra gold key.

104
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:25,600
Okay.

105
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:25,840
Good.

106
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,520
That works.

107
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,300
(Exactly what I wanted)

108
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:29,320
(Ding: flashlight, Zhang: solo mission card)
These rewards

109
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:29,800
(Jin: gold keys, Zhou: make Ding do a solo mission)
are meant to motivate us

110
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,960
(Liu: 3 days check-in on fan community page)
more to go find

111
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:31,920
that key evidence.

112
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,520
It feels like in all the seasons
we're recorded,

113
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,320
we've never actually managed to find it.

114
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,040
Yes, that's right.

115
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:40,320
But recently, we've come pretty close.

116
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,360
Ning.

117
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,280
Ning even checked

118
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,000
inside the trash bin.

119
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,160
No, last time we checked the trash bin

120
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,560
and that bag inside...

121
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,320
But we still didn't find it.

122
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:48,640
I even asked He,

123
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:49,240
why do you have

124
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,680
so many tissues

125
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,480
in your room?

126
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:52,720
She said it's because of his rhinitis.

127
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:53,360
I said,

128
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,080
Oh, rhinitis.

129
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:57,580
(Missed evidence)

130
00:03:59,160 --> 00:03:59,840
I think

131
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,120
I need to change my wish.

132
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,320
If I get a gold key,

133
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:03,720
I'm going to request a doctor online

134
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,480
to cure his rhinitis completely.

135
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,920
So you're basically
trying to summon a doctor online?

136
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,280
(Loading archive…)
Second case archive ended.

137
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:13,960
(Case 2: Oh No, Not the Puppet)

138
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:14,960
(Case 3: The Price of 0.99)
Now retrieving archive

139
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,070
for Case 3.

140
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,270
(Case 3: The Price of 0.99)
Week 3.

141
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:19,940
(Open for business)

142
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,360
It's the Starlight Cafe.

143
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:22,540
(Impressive memory)

144
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:29,140
(I want to drink)

145
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,440
(Absorbed by beauty)
So pretty.

146
00:04:39,810 --> 00:04:42,160
Today's coffee beans are really good.

147
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:44,520
Who is this?

148
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,800
Is your spine okay?

149
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,120
Scoliosis.

150
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,520
So pretty.

151
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,560
Is she a foreigner?

152
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,860
(Shocked by own beauty again)

153
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,580
(As expected of you, no OOC at all)

154
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:56,620
(Jin Cardashian)

155
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:57,920
I'm coughing...

156
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:58,960
coughing...

157
00:04:58,960 --> 00:04:59,520
coughing up phlegm.

158
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:02,620
Alright,

159
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:03,900
stop pretending.

160
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:05,260
I know...

161
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:07,360
you've been waiting for me.

162
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:10,160
(Checking which VIP it is)

163
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:14,900
(The sequel to Exaggerated Life)
Let me check.

164
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:16,000
Alright.

165
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,540
First,

166
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:20,150
(Ning Bubble)
a lemon sparkling Americano.

167
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:23,020
(Wow)

168
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,750
Barista Ning Bubble.

169
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:26,590
He blends his bubble voice

170
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:27,780
into every cup

171
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:29,380
of lemon sparkling Americano.

172
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:30,660
Fresh.

173
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:31,490
Controlled.

174
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,910
But strangely intoxicating.

175
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:36,260
(Barista Ning Bubble)

176
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:37,310
Jin,

177
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:39,930
(Lemon sparkling Americano)
your mood special for today

178
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:41,290
is this...

179
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:44,580
lemon sparkling Americano.

180
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:48,080
I've fainted.

181
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:49,520
If you want to wake me up,

182
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:53,160
you have to call my name
ten thousand times

183
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,490
using your bubble voice.

184
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,440
Just stay asleep then.

185
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:57,700
(Oh?)

186
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:58,540
(Bubble loading…)

187
00:05:58,540 --> 00:05:59,940
(Every night)

188
00:05:59,940 --> 00:06:01,820
(I call your name)

189
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:03,660
(ten thousand times)

190
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:04,490
(Buzzed on bubbles)

191
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:08,100
(Exclusive live performance)
♪All I think about is you♪

192
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:12,040
(Upgraded emotional state)
♪All about you♪

193
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:15,500
(Even my toes are toes)

194
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:19,420
(This is too entertaining)

195
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:22,000
Let out a refreshing burp.

196
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,300
Next drink, I'll order

197
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,860
an Espresso Martini.

198
00:06:24,860 --> 00:06:25,940
(Oh wow)

199
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:27,540
(He Yiwei)

200
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,160
How did you spin that so nicely?

201
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:32,320
Skill.

202
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,080
You secretly designing it yourself.

203
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:37,510
(You're pretty much serving looks, huh?)

204
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,620
He stands there

205
00:06:38,620 --> 00:06:40,150
like a freshly made

206
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,080
Espresso Martini.

207
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,840
Bro.

208
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,900
(He Yiwei)

209
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:48,760
(This is too much)

210
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,520
There's even a wink.

211
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:52,340
(Shy)
Your Espresso Martini is ready.

212
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,860
So handsome, bro.

213
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:55,740
(Jin Cardashian played by Jin Jing)

214
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:56,960
This is your first time meeting me?

215
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,520
You can't talk like that.

216
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:01,920
No, you're handsome.

217
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,680
That's for sure.

218
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,360
But you can't act like you know
you're handsome.

219
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,160
You must...

220
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:05,480
Alright.

221
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,280
Remember this.

222
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,080
Okay.

223
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:07,360
Yes.

224
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,440
The glass is going to spill.

225
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:08,960
It's about to spill.

226
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:09,340
(Scene warning)

227
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:09,980
(What level is this, sitting with me?)

228
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,100
(It's chaos)

229
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,100
Come on.

230
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:13,820
(I'm immune to coffee now)

231
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,740
(My bubble)

232
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:20,260
(Look how anxious we both are)

233
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,400
Where did Ding go?

234
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,180
(Wants to help but confused)
Where's the mop?

235
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,680
You're still thinking about cleaning.

236
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,480
(Responsible since young)
That's impressive.

237
00:07:25,540 --> 00:07:27,780
(Dedicated shop assistant Ding Pudding)
She just wants my drink.

238
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:28,380
Quick.

239
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,230
(Hot-hearted coworker)
Quick, grab me.

240
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:30,670
(How dare you steal from me)
He's stealing over me.

241
00:07:30,670 --> 00:07:32,090
You also have to pull me over
and fight for me.

242
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:33,250
(Acting mode)

243
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,260
Keep going.

244
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:35,410
(Playing along)
Alright.

245
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,340
That's enough.

246
00:07:36,340 --> 00:07:36,760
Come here.

247
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,300
No.

248
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:37,600
Alright.

249
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:37,940
I love them all.

250
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:39,140
(Please control yourself)
Jin, please sit.

251
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:39,980
(Enjoying the performance)

252
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:41,070
Next drink.

253
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,720
Let's have something sweet.

254
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:44,920
(Ding Pudding)
Pudding coffee.

255
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:45,950
Ding Pudding.

256
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,440
Ding Pudding.

257
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:50,420
Barista Ding Pudding.

258
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,720
So cute.

259
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,040
Being young is nice.

260
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:55,260
(Age makes people sentimental)

261
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:59,160
He looks so youthful.

262
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:02,580
(So youthful)
First sip is fresh, second sip turns sweet.

263
00:08:02,910 --> 00:08:04,900
Before you realize it,
it's already stuck in your heart.

264
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,580
(Barista Ding Pudding)

265
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,760
Ding Pudding.

266
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:10,560
Jin.

267
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,640
Which year were you born?

268
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:13,960
1998.

269
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,040
(Born in 2002, self-defined age twist)

270
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,600
1998? Really?

271
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:18,240
Which month in 2002 were you born?

272
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,880
February. I'm older than you.

273
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:20,920
Not 2000?

274
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:21,680
I'm not 2000.

275
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,680
You're 1998?

276
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,120
Yes.

277
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,440
How is that possible?

278
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:26,160
(I don't believe)

279
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,760
He's same as Keyu.

280
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:30,040
(Both born in 2002)
Don't believe him.

