00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:17,400
The part after we ate at the cafeteria.

1397
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:19,360
The one with the giant metal ball.

1398
00:40:20,100 --> 00:40:21,580
(Cafeteria)

1399
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:22,360
(Level-one security alert.
Self-destruct mode activated)

1400
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:24,010
Self-destruct?

1401
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,790
Self-destruct mode?

1402
00:40:25,790 --> 00:40:26,450
(The boss' death triggered)
Self-destruct mode!

1403
00:40:26,450 --> 00:40:27,120
(the base's self-destruct mode)
Self-destruct mode!

1404
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:27,810
Let's go!

1405
00:40:29,660 --> 00:40:30,580
(Taking two bites to calm down)

1406
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:31,720
This was really scary.

1407
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,080
What if someone had been there?

1408
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,360
No, they were watching.

1409
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:36,920
Yeah.

1410
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,080
Unless you just

1411
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:40,200
ran over there yourself.

1412
00:40:40,260 --> 00:40:41,380
(Yeah, let's not)

1413
00:40:41,730 --> 00:40:42,600
Go down here.

1414
00:40:43,140 --> 00:40:44,600
Dude, down here?

1415
00:40:45,300 --> 00:40:46,700
Yeah, down here.

1416
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:48,420
(A channel to an unknown area appears)

1417
00:40:48,420 --> 00:40:49,180
We have to go.

1418
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:50,100
Hurry!

1419
00:40:50,100 --> 00:40:51,020
Be careful.

1420
00:40:51,020 --> 00:40:51,860
Watch out!

1421
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,480
Were you scared then,

1422
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:54,840
Ding?

1423
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:55,400
No.

1424
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:56,080
This kind doesn't scare you?

1425
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:57,040
It's this bright. What am I scared of?

1426
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,700
(King of daylight, after all)
So adventure stuff doesn't scare you.

1427
00:40:58,800 --> 00:40:59,880
He's just scared of the dark.

1428
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:01,440
I'm only scared of the dark.

1429
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:08,640
Look at that.

1430
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:09,640
We've got stamina.

1431
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:12,320
We've got excitement.

1432
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:15,400
No, I mean our team.

1433
00:41:16,660 --> 00:41:21,620
We can dance, sing, and we've
got stamina, looks, and brains.

1434
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,080
That's it?

1435
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:23,440
What else?

1436
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:23,880
What about me?

1437
00:41:24,460 --> 00:41:26,420
Looks.

1438
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:26,820
I'm that one.

1439
00:41:26,820 --> 00:41:27,380
Brains.

1440
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:27,920
Aren't those all you?

1441
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:28,960
(Got praised into a smug grin)

1442
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:29,680
What else do you want?

1443
00:41:30,840 --> 00:41:32,320
We're pushing the iron ball.

1444
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:33,160
(Weight-sensing zone)

1445
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:34,400
Weight sensor.

1446
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:35,640
That was seriously tiring.

1447
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:38,710
Hello, I'm Tui WANGWANG.

1448
00:41:38,980 --> 00:41:39,870
Tui what?

1449
00:41:39,870 --> 00:41:40,840
(Tui Wangwang? Tui Light?)
Tui what?

1450
00:41:41,380 --> 00:41:42,140
(Tui Guangguang)

1451
00:41:42,300 --> 00:41:42,820
(Master of mishearing)

1452
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:43,400
Tui Guangguang.

1453
00:41:43,400 --> 00:41:44,600
Hello, I'm Tui WANGWANG.

1454
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:45,840
(Forgot again)
It's called Tui Light.

1455
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,440
Tui WANGWANG.

1456
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:48,570
(No response)

1457
00:41:48,600 --> 00:41:49,660
(Successfully activated)
Are you calling me?

1458
00:41:49,660 --> 00:41:50,370
Yes.

1459
00:41:50,370 --> 00:41:51,230
I'm here.

1460
00:41:51,230 --> 00:41:52,090
Whenever you need me,

1461
00:41:52,090 --> 00:41:53,160
- I'll always be here.
- Tui WANGWANG.

1462
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:54,330
(Cafe conspiracy: 70% complete)
That's how it works. Come on.

1463
00:41:54,330 --> 00:41:55,550
Okay, let's push it. Got it.

1464
00:41:55,550 --> 00:41:56,640
Okay, let's get one up first.

1465
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:57,010
Come on.

1466
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:58,800
Thought it was easy.

1467
00:41:58,800 --> 00:41:59,520
Push one up first.

1468
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:00,720
(Steep ramp)

1469
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:01,760
Looks like nothing.

1470
00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:02,940
(Sounds casual, but they're
actually out of ideas)

1471
00:42:02,940 --> 00:42:04,140
(Super-heavy iron ball)

1472
00:42:04,850 --> 00:42:06,030
It's heavier than I thought.

1473
00:42:06,780 --> 00:42:07,780
(Powerhouse up front)

1474
00:42:07,780 --> 00:42:10,780
(Back row ready to assist)

1475
00:42:13,880 --> 00:42:15,400
The main thing is, we were
pushing with our left hands.

1476
00:42:15,740 --> 00:42:16,800
(Reviewing: hard to push
with the left hand)

1477
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:17,480
Right.

1478
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:19,280
Left hand is too hard.

1479
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:21,820
Ding can do it.

1480
00:42:21,820 --> 00:42:22,700
(Hey, wait!)

1481
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:24,520
Wait.

1482
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:26,440
Powering through.

1483
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:27,620
(Powering forward)

1484
00:42:27,620 --> 00:42:28,910
Those two...

1485
00:42:28,910 --> 00:42:30,240
They can get it up by themselves.

1486
00:42:30,240 --> 00:42:31,420
(Unstoppable)

1487
00:42:31,420 --> 00:42:33,100
(Shocked again)

1488
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:35,240
After Ding pushed that one ball,

1489
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:36,400
he used up too much energy.

1490
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:36,960
Yeah.

1491
00:42:36,960 --> 00:42:37,440
Right.

1492
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:38,000
I was

1493
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:38,840
completely

1494
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:39,560
wiped out.

1495
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,480
He was out of strength after one push.

1496
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,720
There were four in total.

1497
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:44,880
Because once you get halfway,
you can't stop.

1498
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:45,320
At first,

1499
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:47,160
we hadn't figured out the force

1500
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:48,040
or the...

1501
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:49,140
Trick to it.

1502
00:42:49,140 --> 00:42:49,900
(If the code works, don't touch it)

1503
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:51,820
I was totally overheating.

1504
00:42:51,820 --> 00:42:52,380
(Eyes locked on)

1505
00:42:52,880 --> 00:42:53,200
For real.

1506
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,040
Nice.

1507
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:00,320
Awesome.

1508
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:01,640
So strong.

1509
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:06,740
Ding.

1510
00:43:06,740 --> 00:43:08,900
(Elevator descends. One light turns on.)

1511
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:10,000
Okay, it came down a bit.

1512
00:43:11,300 --> 00:43:12,420
(Feeling bad for little me back then)

1513
00:43:12,420 --> 00:43:14,380
(Progress: 1/4)

1514
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:15,360
What?

1515
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:16,800
No way.

1516
00:43:16,800 --> 00:43:17,440
Let's go, Ke.

1517
00:43:17,940 --> 00:43:18,320
Come on, Ning.

1518
00:43:19,220 --> 00:43:20,020
I'll go in front, okay?

1519
00:43:20,020 --> 00:43:21,310
Okay, I'll support you.

1520
00:43:22,770 --> 00:43:24,300
(Eager to help)
Be careful this time.

1521
00:43:24,780 --> 00:43:25,660
Push left.

1522
00:43:27,130 --> 00:43:28,600
(Young genius shows off his strength)
I've got you.

1523
00:43:32,080 --> 00:43:33,580
(Great progress)
Slow down. No rush.

1524
00:43:33,700 --> 00:43:35,180
(Ready to catch them)

1525
00:43:36,620 --> 00:43:37,900
(Slipping)

1526
00:43:38,020 --> 00:43:38,540
(Hold it!)

1527
00:43:38,630 --> 00:43:39,380
You're good.

1528
00:43:39,700 --> 00:43:40,860
(My size 11s have you covered)

1529
00:43:40,860 --> 00:43:42,150
You can use both hands.

1530
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:44,480
Later, one of us pulled from the front,

1531
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:45,600
and one pushed from behind.

1532
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:47,200
Honestly, both were pretty hard.

1533
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:48,120
It's basically the same.

1534
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:49,980
(Same thing)

1535
00:43:49,980 --> 00:43:51,120
(Single rhyme)
That's just how you do it.

1536
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:52,600
You just have to force it up.

1537
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:53,080
Just force it up.

1538
00:43:55,300 --> 00:43:57,700
(Giving it everything)

1539
00:44:00,340 --> 00:44:01,580
(It won't budge)
We'll bring you another ball.

1540
00:44:01,580 --> 00:44:02,610
We can only get it this far.

1541
00:44:02,890 --> 00:44:03,810
You two...

1542
00:44:05,020 --> 00:44:06,180
(Danger)
Don't let go!

1543
00:44:06,510 --> 00:44:07,390
Don't let go!

1544
00:44:07,390 --> 00:44:08,260
No, move away.

1545
00:44:08,260 --> 00:44:09,300
Move away first.

1546
00:44:11,850 --> 00:44:12,410
I'll come down.

1547
00:44:12,410 --> 00:44:13,270
I'm coming down.

1548
00:44:14,720 --> 00:44:15,280
Let's go.

1549
00:44:15,280 --> 00:44:15,780
Come on.

1550
00:44:19,060 --> 00:44:19,820
(Friendly reminder: you can breathe)

1551
00:44:19,820 --> 00:44:20,580
(Stacking more power)

1552
00:44:20,580 --> 00:44:22,340
(Human conveyor belt)

1553
00:44:22,360 --> 00:44:24,080
Even with Ning and me pushing together,
we couldn't move him.

1554
00:44:24,680 --> 00:44:25,520
He wouldn't budge.

1555
00:44:30,680 --> 00:44:32,100
Why don't you switch out?

1556
00:44:32,100 --> 00:44:32,750
Okay.

1557
00:44:32,750 --> 00:44:33,520
Come on!

1558
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:34,170
Almost there.

1559
00:44:34,660 --> 00:44:35,940
(Relay push)

1560
00:44:35,940 --> 00:44:37,340
(Steering from above)

1561
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:38,960
No matter how hard the people
behind push,

1562
00:44:39,360 --> 00:44:41,280
the person in front still
has to use his own strength.

1563
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:43,040
Right. He still
has to inch forward himself.

1564
00:44:43,040 --> 00:44:44,320
The people behind him

1565
00:44:44,320 --> 00:44:46,040
are just keeping him from sliding back.

1566
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,520
Just keeping him from falling.

1567
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:48,120
Right.

1568
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:50,960
I'm tired just watching.

1569
00:44:52,400 --> 00:44:53,560
Brace their foot.

1570
00:44:53,560 --> 00:44:54,030
Push hard.

1571
00:44:54,120 --> 00:44:55,560
Almost there.

1572
00:44:56,020 --> 00:44:57,550
(Foot: Let me help)
I've got you.

1573
00:44:57,550 --> 00:44:59,000
(Helping with a foot)
Yeah, push back.

1574
00:44:59,000 --> 00:44:59,920
There are people behind you.

1575
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:01,210
Keep moving up.

1576
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:03,150
How about I...

1577
00:45:03,150 --> 00:45:03,550
Come on.

1578
00:45:03,550 --> 00:45:04,220
Three, two, one.

1579
00:45:04,220 --> 00:45:05,920
Three, two, one. Switch!

1580
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:06,990
Three, two, one.

1581
00:45:06,990 --> 00:45:08,440
Three, two, one. Switch!

1582
00:45:08,440 --> 00:45:09,060
Come on.

1583
00:45:09,060 --> 00:45:10,550
One, two, three. Go!

1584
00:45:10,550 --> 00:45:11,420
Okay.

1585
00:45:11,420 --> 00:45:11,980
Go!

1586
00:45:11,980 --> 00:45:12,460
Push!

1587
00:45:13,540 --> 00:45:14,540
(Three, two, one. Go!)

1588
00:45:14,540 --> 00:45:16,300
(Powered by yelling)

1589
00:45:16,300 --> 00:45:17,230
To the right.

1590
00:45:17,230 --> 00:45:17,990
Push it right.

1591
00:45:17,990 --> 00:45:19,200
Three, two, one. Go!

1592
00:45:19,940 --> 00:45:21,860
(NO WAY)

1593
00:45:22,060 --> 00:45:23,260
(Everyone pushes together)

1594
00:45:23,260 --> 00:45:23,840
Go!

1595
00:45:24,830 --> 00:45:26,020
Three, two, one!

1596
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,920
Leave it to Ding.

1597
00:45:28,840 --> 00:45:30,360
Ding is seriously strong.

1598
00:45:30,360 --> 00:45:31,440
You can't tell, right?

1599
00:45:31,440 --> 00:45:32,680
He's actually pretty built.

1600
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:33,600
For real.

1601
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:34,480
Yeah. He's strong.

1602
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:37,380
(Super-strong sweetie)

1603
00:45:40,150 --> 00:45:41,510
Let's do it.

1604
00:45:41,510 --> 00:45:42,450
Come on.

1605
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,070
This is way too hard.

1606
00:45:44,070 --> 00:45:45,410
Just let it out. You'll be fine.

1607
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:47,910
Go crazy or go home.

1608
00:45:49,640 --> 00:45:50,520
Why so cool?

1609
00:45:53,560 --> 00:45:54,360
Why so cool?

1610
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:02,470
Stay safe.

1611
00:46:02,470 --> 00:46:03,040
You got this!

1612
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:03,900
(Got the rhythm. Just shake it)
Let's go!

1613
00:46:03,900 --> 00:46:05,330
Alright, we're counting
on you down there.

1614
00:46:08,120 --> 00:46:09,280
Search while engaging.

1615
00:46:09,280 --> 00:46:10,560
Finish it and fall back.

1616
00:46:11,240 --> 00:46:11,600
What?

1617
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:12,600
Nothing.

1618
00:46:12,620 --> 00:46:13,530
Can you hear us?

1619
00:46:13,530 --> 00:46:14,110
Yes.

1620
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:15,160
It's a gaming meme.

1621
00:46:15,340 --> 00:46:17,820
(Sorry to bother you)

1622
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:19,760
♪Let's begin tonight♪

1623
00:46:20,180 --> 00:46:20,960
(Already hyped himself up)

1624
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:23,070
♪Search for the vanished cipher♪

1625
00:46:23,070 --> 00:46:24,080
Guys, start going down.

1626
00:46:24,080 --> 00:46:26,400
♪Let courage spark the dark♪

1627
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:26,930
Okay, let's do it.

1628
00:46:26,930 --> 00:46:28,200
Three, two, one, go!

1629
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:30,040
I didn't even see this part.

1630
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:31,720
Let's see how cool it was.

1631
00:46:31,740 --> 00:46:33,980
(Eyes are ready)

1632
00:46:36,400 --> 00:46:37,080
The wide shot looks cool.

1633
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:40,200
I was actually really scared.

1634
00:46:40,640 --> 00:46:41,160
Really?

1635
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:42,480
I was seriously scared.

1636
00:46:43,000 --> 00:46:44,360
But when I was up there,

1637
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,960
the three of them

1638
00:46:45,960 --> 00:46:46,840
went down so fast.

1639
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:47,640
They said, "Let's go"!

1640
00:46:47,640 --> 00:46:47,960
"Hurry"!

1641
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:48,640
"Go"!

1642
00:46:48,640 --> 00:46:49,120
Then I said,

1643
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:50,240
"I still need to mentally prepare".

1644
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:51,320
Then I was like, "Forget it. Let's go".

1645
00:46:51,680 --> 00:46:52,120
See?

1646
00:46:52,120 --> 00:46:53,280
I was the last one down.

1647
00:46:53,380 --> 00:46:55,020
(Starting to feel it too)

1648
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:57,280
Mainly because the three
of us tried it last year.

1649
00:46:57,420 --> 00:46:59,340
(The Truth Season 3, Episode 6 Part 2)

1650
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:00,560
It's Ding's first time playing.

1651
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:00,920
Yes.

1652
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:02,140
(First time trying abseiling)

1653
00:47:02,390 --> 00:47:02,800
Two.

1654
00:47:04,140 --> 00:47:04,890
One.

1655
00:47:05,180 --> 00:47:05,790
Go!

1656
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:08,460
Go!

1657
00:47:08,460 --> 00:47:08,780
Not bad.

1658
00:47:08,780 --> 00:47:09,780
(Loud shout)

1659
00:47:17,460 --> 00:47:18,740
(Woah!)

1660
00:47:19,100 --> 00:47:20,300
(Silent wow. Loud wow)

1661
00:47:23,660 --> 00:47:24,740
(Ke Coffee's POV)

1662
00:47:24,900 --> 00:47:25,980
(Ning Bubble's POV)

1663
00:47:26,140 --> 00:47:26,860
(He Yiwei's POV)

1664
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:28,360
(Ding Pudding's POV)
So cool.

1665
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:37,160
There's more.

1666
00:47:38,820 --> 00:47:41,620
(Impressed by his own good looks)

1667
00:47:55,920 --> 00:47:57,270
So handsome!

1668
00:47:57,800 --> 00:47:58,940
Let's go!

1669
00:48:01,840 --> 00:48:04,090
Guys, that was amazing.

1670
00:48:04,860 --> 00:48:06,260
(Loving this)

1671
00:48:06,640 --> 00:48:07,080
Not bad.

1672
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:08,240
It was cool.

1673
